{"news_desk": "Foreign", "print_page": "1", "section_name": "World", "subsection_name": "Middle East", "byline": {"original": "By MARK MAZZETTI and HELENE COOPER", "person": [{"rank": 1, "role": "reported", "firstname": "Mark", "organization": "", "lastname": "MAZZETTI"}, {"rank": 2, "role": "reported", "firstname": "Helene", "organization": "", "lastname": "COOPER"}]}, "abstract": "Descent of Middle East into number of proxy wars, sectarian conflict and fights to limit influence of terrorist groups has resulted in boom for American defense industry hoping to make up for smaller Pentagon budgets; number of requests for military hardware has raised fears of dangerous arms race in region, particularly because restrictions on arms sales, in place to protect Israel, have been relaxed.", "type_of_material": "News", "word_count": "1308", "lead_paragraph": "A de facto alliance in the region against Iran has opened the way to more sales to Arab states, and raised fears of an arms race.", "pub_date": "2015-04-19T00:00:00Z", "document_type": "article", "slideshow_credits": null, "headline": {"main": "Sale of U.S. Arms Fuels the Wars of Arab States", "print_headline": "Sale of U.S. Arms Fuels the Wars of Arab States"}, "snippet": "A de facto alliance in the region against Iran has opened the way to more sales to Arab states, and raised fears of an arms race.", "multimedia": [{"height": 126, "url": "images/2015/04/19/world/SUB-JP-ARMS/SUB-JP-ARMS-thumbWide.jpg", "legacy": {"widewidth": "190", "wideheight": "126", "wide": "images/2015/04/19/world/SUB-JP-ARMS/SUB-JP-ARMS-thumbWide.jpg"}, "type": "image", "width": 190, "subtype": "wide"}, {"height": 376, "url": "images/2015/04/19/world/SUB-JP-ARMS/SUB-JP-ARMS-articleLarge.jpg", "legacy": {"xlargewidth": "600", "xlargeheight": "376", "xlarge": "images/2015/04/19/world/SUB-JP-ARMS/SUB-JP-ARMS-articleLarge.jpg"}, "type": "image", "width": 600, "subtype": "xlarge"}, {"height": 75, "url": "images/2015/04/19/world/SUB-JP-ARMS/SUB-JP-ARM